stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> READY
    READY --> RUNNING: command starts
    RUNNING --> MDL_WAITING: metadata conflict
    RUNNING --> ROW_LOCK_WAITING: storage row lock conflict
    RUNNING --> STREAMING: result metadata sent
    RUNNING --> CLEANING: normal completion
    MDL_WAITING --> RUNNING: grant
    ROW_LOCK_WAITING --> RUNNING: grant and relocate
    STREAMING --> CLEANING: result exhausted

    READY --> CLOSING: COM_QUIT or disconnect
    RUNNING --> KILL_QUERY_MARKED: KILL QUERY flag set
    MDL_WAITING --> KILL_QUERY_MARKED: kill checkpoint
    ROW_LOCK_WAITING --> KILL_QUERY_MARKED: kill checkpoint
    STREAMING --> KILL_QUERY_MARKED: kill checkpoint
    KILL_QUERY_MARKED --> STATEMENT_ROLLBACK: abort current statement
    STATEMENT_ROLLBACK --> CLEANING: release statement resources
    CLEANING --> READY: query killed, connection remains

    READY --> KILL_CONNECTION_MARKED: KILL CONNECTION flag set
    RUNNING --> KILL_CONNECTION_MARKED: KILL CONNECTION flag set
    STREAMING --> KILL_CONNECTION_MARKED: KILL CONNECTION flag set
    KILL_CONNECTION_MARKED --> STATEMENT_ROLLBACK: abort current statement
    CLEANING --> SESSION_CLEANUP: connection close requested
    CLOSING --> SESSION_CLEANUP: no active statement
    SESSION_CLEANUP --> ROLLBACK_OPEN_TX: open transaction exists
    SESSION_CLEANUP --> CLOSE_PREPARED: no open transaction
    ROLLBACK_OPEN_TX --> CLOSE_PREPARED
    CLOSE_PREPARED --> RELEASE_SESSION_RESOURCES
    RELEASE_SESSION_RESOURCES --> CLOSED
    CLOSED --> [*]

    note right of KILL_QUERY_MARKED
      KILL QUERY keeps the session.
      Prepared handles remain but execution resources are released.
    end note

    note right of SESSION_CLEANUP
      Cleanup is idempotent for kill,
      disconnect, timeout, and command failure.
    end note
